Types:
	1) SDL_Surface:
		fildes: ->format->BitsPerPixel
		creators: SDL_SetVideoMode, SDL_LoadBMP(char *file_name)

		example: 
			    /* Have a preference for 8-bit, but accept any depth */
			    screen = SDL_SetVideoMode(640, 480, 8, SDL_SWSURFACE|SDL_ANYFORMAT);
	2)SDL_Rect:


Functions:
	1)SDL_Surface* SDL_SetVideoMode(int width, int height, int bitsperpixel, Uint32 flags);
		Flags:
			SDL_HWSURFACE is set in 'flags', the video surface will be placed in
			 * video memory, if possible, and you may have to call SDL_LockSurface()
			 * in order to access the raw framebuffer.  Otherwise, the video surface
			 * will be created in system memory
		explanation:
			http://sdl.beuc.net/sdl.wiki/SDL_SetVideoMode
	2)int SDL_BlitSurface(SDL_Surface* src, const SDL_Rect* srcrect, SDL_Surface* dst, SDL_Rect* dstrect)
		explanations:
			src = img to be copied on the srcrect
			srcrect = rec that the src (img) will be copied to (entered has a pointer using &)
			dst = the surface that the srcrect will be puted in
			dstrect = 
			https://wiki.libsdl.org/SDL_BlitSurface

	3)int SDL_SetColors(SDL_Surface *surface, SDL_Color *colors, int firstcolor, int ncolors)
		explanation:
			https://www.libsdl.org/release/SDL-1.2.15/docs/html/sdlsetcolors.html
	4) SDL_Delay(int milisec)
		exp: Wait a specified number of milliseconds before returning
	5)SDL_FreeSurface(SDL_FreeSurface* surface)
	6)SDL_SetVideoMode(int width, int height, int bpp, Uint32 flags)
	  explanation:
		https://www.libsdl.org/release/SDL-1.2.15/docs/html/sdlsetvideomode.html
